6.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Carleton was born in 1464, in Kirton, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Mrs Thomas Carleton."},"et":{"<1464>–":"1464–Surnud","1468–Female":"1468–Surnud","1493–1527":"1493–1527","1495–1538":"1495–1538","1497–Male":"1497–Surnud","1464–Male":"1464–Surnud","1468":"1468","1497":"1497","1464":"1464","Abt 1495":"umbes 1495","1495":"1495","1493":"1493","<1464>":"1464","about 1493":"umbes 1493","1538":"1538","1527":"1527","Wakefield, Yorkshire, England":"Wakefield St Mary, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kirton, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Kirton, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"<1464>–":"1464–Kuollut","1468–Female":"1468–Kuollut","1493–1527":"1493–1527","1495–1538":"1495–1538","1497–Male":"1497–Kuollut","1464–Male":"1464–Kuollut","1468":"1468","1497":"1497","1464":"1464","Abt 1495":"noin 1495","1495":"1495","1493":"1493","<1464>":"1464","about 1493":"noin 1493","1538":"1538","1527":"1527","Wakefield, Yorkshire, England":"Wakefield St Mary, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kirton, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Kirton, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"<1464>–":"1464–Décédé","1468–Female":"1468–Décédée","1493–1527":"1493–1527","1495–1538":"1495–1538","1497–Male":"1497–Décédé","1464–Male":"1464–Décédé","1468":"1468","1497":"1497","1464":"1464","Abt 1495":"environ 1495","1495":"1495","1493":"1493","<1464>":"1464","about 1493":"environ 1493","1538":"1538","1527":"1527","Wakefield, Yorkshire, England":"Wakefield St Mary, Ev